The paper deals with the problem of answering queries on a private database while protecting differential privacy for both the individuals in the database and the analysts. This falls under the category of privacy-preserving data analysis, which is typically covered in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces a novel view of the problem as a two-player zero-sum game, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves techniques for handling non-linear queries, which could be relevant to researchers in cs.IT (Information Theory).
